window.docContents[92].resolve({"/Terms/Numeric-Literals/#zh-terms-h011":{"contents":"科学数字文字由一系列十进制数字组成，后跟（不插入空格）可选的小数部分（句号后跟零个或多个十进制数字）和可选的指数部分（字母 e 后跟可选的 + 或 -，然后后跟一个或多个十进制数字）。\n科学数字通过 OfScientific 类型类重载。\n\nFor decimal and scientific numbers (e.g., 1.23, 3.12e10).\nExamples:* 1.23 is syntax for OfScientific.ofScientific (nat_lit 123) true (nat_lit 2)* 121e100 is syntax for OfScientific.ofScientific (nat_lit 121) false (nat_lit 100)Note the use of nat_lit; there is no wrapping OfNat.ofNat in the resulting term.Produces a value from the given mantissa, exponent sign, and decimal exponent. For the exponent\nsign, true indicates a negative exponent.Examples:* 1.23 is syntax for OfScientific.ofScientific (nat_lit 123) true (nat_lit 2)* 121e100 is syntax for OfScientific.ofScientific (nat_lit 121) false (nat_lit 100)Note the use of nat_lit; there is no wrapping OfNat.ofNat in the resulting term.\n\nFloat 和 Float32 有一个 OfScientific 实例，但没有单独的浮点文字。\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009条款\u0009数字文字","header":"13.5.2. 科学数字","id":"/Terms/Numeric-Literals/#zh-terms-h011"},"/The-Simplifier/Terminal-vs-Non-Terminal-Positions/#terminal-simp":{"contents":"要编写可维护的证明，请避免使用不带 only 的 simp，除非它关闭了目标。\n不关闭目标的 simp 的此类使用称为 non-terminal simps。\n这是因为对默认 simp 集的添加可能会使 simp 更强大，或者只是导致它选择不同的重写序列并达到不同的 simp 范式。\n当指定 only 时，其他引理将不会影响策略的调用。\n实际上，simp 的终端使用不太可能因添加新的 simpl 引理而被破坏，并且当它们被破坏时，更容易理解问题并修复它。\n\n在非终端位置工作时，simp?（或名称中带有 ? 的其他简化策略之一）可用于生成 only 的适当调用。\n正如 apply? 或 rw? 建议使用相关引理一样，simp? 建议使用用于达到规范形式的最小 simp 集来调用 simp。\n\nUsing simp?此证明中的非终结符 simp? 建议使用更小的 simp 和 only：example (xs : Array Unit) : xs.size = 2 → xs = #[(), ()] := by\n  intros\n  ext\n  simp?\n  assumption\n建议的重写是：Try this:\n  [apply] simp only [List.size_toArray, List.length_cons, List.length_nil, Nat.zero_add, Nat.reduceAdd]\n这导致了更易于维护的证明：example (xs : Array Unit) : xs.size = 2 → xs = #[(), ()] := by\n  intros\n  ext\n  simp only [\n    List.size_toArray, List.length_cons, List.length_nil,\n    Nat.zero_add, Nat.reduceAdd\n  ]\n  assumption\n\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009简化者","header":"15.5. 终端头寸与非终端头寸","id":"/The-Simplifier/Terminal-vs-Non-Terminal-Positions/#terminal-simp"},"/Type-Classes/Instance-Synthesis/#zh-classes-instancesynth-h009":{"contents":"use optimization that relies on 'morally canonical' instances during type class resolution\n\nmaximum amount of heartbeats per typeclass resolution problem. A heartbeat is number of (small) memory allocations (in thousands), 0 means no limit\n\nmaximum number of instances used to construct a solution in the type class instance synthesis procedure\n\nwrap instance bodies in inferInstanceAs and the default deriving handler\n\nwhen recursing into sub-instances, reuse existing instances for the target type instead of re-wrapping them, which can be important to avoid non-defeq instance diamonds\n\nwrap non-reducible instances in auxiliary definitions to fix their types\n\nwrap data fields in auxiliary definitions to fix their types\n\n","context":"Lean 参考\u0009Type 类别\u0009实例合成","header":"10.3.9. 选项","id":"/Type-Classes/Instance-Synthesis/#zh-classes-instancesynth-h009"}});